,{"categoryHTML":"<h2>What is this about?</h2><h3>Repos</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/busypeoples/functional-programming-javascript\">Functional Programming In JavaScript</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/busypeoples/functional-programming-javascript\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">285</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":285,\"repo\":\"busypeoples/functional-programming-javascript\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - List of functional programming resources in JavaScript.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-12-07T02:39:30.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>What is this about?</h2><h3>Papers</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://isabelle.in.tum.de/~haftmann/pdf/from_hol_to_haskell_haftmann.pdf\">From Higher-Order Logic to Haskell: There and Back Again</a></li>","updatedAt":"2015-11-30T22:33:19.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>What is this about?</h2><h3>Papers</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://es.cs.uni-kl.de/events/TPHOLs-2007/proceedings/B-178.pdf\">Translating Haskell to Isabelle</a></li>","updatedAt":"2015-11-30T22:33:19.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>What is this about?</h2><h3>Wikis</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Haskell/Category_theory\">Haskell/Category Theory</a> - A good overview on Category Theory applied to Haskell from Wikibooks.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-11-30T22:33:19.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>What is this about?</h2><h3>Wikis</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://wiki.haskell.org/Haskell\">Haskell Wiki</a></li>","updatedAt":"2015-11-30T22:33:19.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>What is this about?</h2><h3>Papers</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.kent.ac.uk/people/staff/dat/miranda/whyfp90.pdf\">Why Functional Programming Matters</a></li>","updatedAt":"2015-11-06T12:57:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>What is this about?</h2><h3>People</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/brianbeckman\">Brian Beckman</a> - Former Microsoft Researcher, actual Software Engineer at Amazon. Contributed to implementing FP features to inumerous Microsoft technologies such as C#, LINQ and F#</li>","updatedAt":"2015-11-03T22:48:36.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>What is this about?</h2><h3>People</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/pub/erik-meijer/0/5ba/924\">Erik Meijer</a> - Former software architect for Microsoft, Functional Programming researcher, gives lectures on\tFP, Software Design and Reactive programming.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-11-03T22:44:25.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>What is this about?</h2><h3>People</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.ccs.neu.edu/home/matthias/\">Matthias Felleisen</a> - Author of many books such as How to Design Programs, and The Little Schemer.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-11-03T22:37:32.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>What is this about?</h2><h3>People</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://homepages.inf.ed.ac.uk/wadler/\">Philip Wadler</a> - Professor of Theoretical Computer Science at the University of Edinburgh, author of the famous paper Propositions as Types. One of the main people behind Java Generics Types.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-11-03T22:34:41.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>What is this about?</h2><h3>People</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://research.microsoft.com/en-us/people/simonpj/\">Simon Peyton Jones</a> - One of the creators of the Haskell Language and the Glasgow Haskell Compiler. Microsoft Researcher.</li>","updatedAt":"2015-11-03T22:29:12.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>What is this about?</h2><h3>B